summary.name: Obesity Rates by State
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains information about obesity rates in different states in the United States.

properties.description: The unique identifier for each record, represented as a timestamp.
The obesity rate in the state, represented as a percentage.
The two-letter abbreviation of the state in the United States.

goals.question: What is the average obesity rate across all states?
goals.visualization: bar chart of average obesity rate per state
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the states with the highest and lowest obesity rates.

goals.question: What is the distribution of obesity rates across all states?
goals.visualization: histogram of obesity rates per state
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the range of obesity rates across all states and the most common obesity rate range.

goals.question: Which state has the highest obesity rate?
goals.visualization: choropleth map of obesity rates per state
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the state with the highest obesity rate and compare it to other states.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between obesity rates and state population?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of obesity rates vs state population
goals.rationale: This helps to identify if there is a relationship between obesity rates and state population.

goals.question: What is the trend of obesity rates over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of obesity rates over time
goals.rationale: This helps to identify if there is a trend of increasing or decreasing obesity rates over time.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='rate', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.axhline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average: {data['rate'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the average obesity rate across all states?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("State")
    plt.ylabel("Obesity Rate")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', bins=10, kde=True, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    median_rate = data['rate'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_rate, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_rate:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of obesity rates across all states?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]

    gdf = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    gdf = gdf[gdf['iso_a2'].isin(['US'])]
    gdf = gdf[['iso_a2', 'geometry']]
    gdf['state'] = data['state']
    gdf['rate'] = data['rate']

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(12, 6))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    gdf.plot(column='rate', cmap='coolwarm', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True, cax=cax)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest obesity rate?', wrap=True)

    max_rate = data['rate'].max()
    max_state = data.loc[data['rate'] == max_rate, 'state'].values[0]
    ax.axhline(max_rate, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Rate: {max_state} ({max_rate:.2f})')
    ax.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='state', y='rate', hue='state', ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    ax.set_title('Is there a correlation between obesity rates and state population?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(title='State', loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.15, 1))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]
    data['year'] = data['id'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='rate', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of obesity rates over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Obesity Rates', loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
